<task id="088" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-D-09 Lightweight Eval Baseline (Q10) — Markdown Conversation Transcripts per Persona + Playbook</title>
    <phase>Phase D — Command Router + Integration + Closeout</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>087</dependencies>
    <blocks>089</blocks>
    <tags>docs, integration-test, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>MINIMAL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Documentation + regression-reference capture per Q10 (R6 lightweight; full harness deferred R7). No code change; MINIMAL per task-create Step 0 rigor tree.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential after vertical-slice; transcripts are best captured from the vertical-slice scenario output.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Capture the lightweight eval baseline per Q10 — markdown conversation transcripts per
    persona + playbook combination, captured as regression references for R6. Full eval harness
    with metrics + CI integration is explicitly deferred to R7 per the spec's Owner Clarifications
    table.

    For each significant persona × playbook combination exercised in R6, capture a markdown
    transcript with the following sections:
    - **Title** (e.g., "SYS-DEFAULT persona × summarize-document-for-chat playbook")
    - **Persona used** (cite `sprk_aipersona` row by name + ID)
    - **Playbook invoked** (cite `sprk_analysisplaybook` row by playbook ID)
    - **User messages** (verbatim conversation user side)
    - **Expected response shape** (per persona + outputSchema)
    - **Actual response (snapshot)** (capture at vertical-slice scenario time)

    Minimum coverage:
    - SYS-DEFAULT persona × `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` (the vertical-slice scenario from
      task 087)
    - SYS-DEFAULT persona × `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`
    - SYS-DEFAULT persona × matter-prefill playbook (NFR-07 binding regression evidence)
    - SYS-DEFAULT persona × project-prefill playbook (NFR-07 binding regression evidence)
    - At least one CUST- persona variant if seeded in any Phase test

    Transcripts live in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/eval-baseline/`.
    Each file is named `{persona}-{playbook}.md`.

    These are reference baselines, not automated tests. R7 will build the full eval harness on
    top of these markdown files (parse them as test fixtures; compute metrics; integrate CI).

    Frontend/BFF code-change delta = 0; BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Documentation + light QA engineer with familiarity with the R6 vertical-slice output +
    persona / playbook combinations. Comfortable with markdown transcript capture conventions.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/eval-baseline/` directory exists with at
    least 4 markdown transcripts covering SYS-DEFAULT × the 4 migrated playbooks (summarize-chat,
    summarize-workspace, matter-prefill, project-prefill). Each transcript follows the standard
    shape (title, persona, playbook, user messages, expected shape, actual snapshot). Q10
    deliverable met; R7 eval-harness team has a working reference baseline.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
